A: It is a complete Linux OS built around the linus kernel. it includes kernel, package manager, utilities

4. pwd command, ls?
A: pwd --> gives present working directory
  ls --> list of files and folders in current directory

5. how to create a directory?
A: pwd 
   for nested directroy (many folders) : mkdir -p /docs/folder1/file1

6. how to remove a directory?
A: to remove a directory: rmdir foldername 
   to remove a directory with files: rm -r foldername
   to remove a directory permenently : rm -rf foldername

7. Diff between rm, rmdir,cd?
A: rm --> removes files and directories
   rmdir --> removes only empty directories
   cd --> changes directory 
8. What is sudo and root?
A: sudo means super user do, and root is a sudo user means it has no restrictions and can perform all tasks

9. explain cp, mv?
A: cp --> copies file content from one to other : cp file1 file2
   mv --> to rename and also move file: rename: mv old.txt new.txt, move: mv file.txt Documents/

